Politics.headline: AI used to reinforce false narratives in Maccabi fan ban – report finds
Politics.detail: A report by the UK Home Affairs Committee found that West Midlands Police were overly reliant on inaccurate, AI-generated information when deciding to ban Maccabi Tel Aviv fans from a Europa League fixture, and that political interference could not be ruled out. The committee also found that the police force failed to engage appropriately with Jewish communities.

Politics.headline: Top News Headlines In Cambodia, Indonesia, Myanmar, Philippines, Singapore, & Vietnam: Feb 22, 2026
Politics.detail: Siem Reap province has been ranked fifth among Asia's Best Cultural Destinations for 2026 by Tripadvisor, a travel platform.

Politics.headline: President Trump has approved a request for federal assistance in response to the massive sewage spill along the Potomac River.
Politics.detail: President Donald Trump has approved a request for federal assistance in response to the massive sewage spill along the Potomac River.

Politics.headline: Argentina's Chamber of Deputies passes controversial labour reform bill
Politics.detail: Argentina's Chamber of Deputies has passed a controversial labour reform bill.

Politics.headline: Federal government says there may not be enough workstations for all workers' 4-day-a-week return
Politics.detail: The Canadian federal government is warning that there may not be enough workstations available for all workers as they transition to a four-day-a-week return to the office.

Finance & Economy.headline: Trump raises global top-up tariff to 15% from 10% after SC ruling
Finance & Economy.detail: Following the Supreme Court's decision against his initial tariffs, President Trump announced a new global tariff increase to 15% from 10%, adding further uncertainty to world trade.

Finance & Economy.headline: US stocks end higher after Supreme Court rules against Trump tariffs
Finance & Economy.detail: Wall Street showed resilience after the Supreme Court's ruling against President Trump's tariffs, with stocks edging higher as the S&P 500 added 0.7%.

Finance & Economy.headline: Pause or peril? Takeaways for the world from Trump's tariff fiasco
Finance & Economy.detail: Analysts are examining the global implications of the Supreme Court's decision to strike down Trump's tariffs, as well as the potential next steps for the U.S. and other world leaders.

Finance & Economy.headline: US economic growth weaker than thought in fourth quarter with government shutdown, consumer pullback.
Finance & Economy.detail: The US economy's growth in the fourth quarter was revised to be weaker than initially estimated due to the government shutdown and reduced consumer spending.

Finance & Economy.headline: Wall Street keeps calm after the Supreme Court strikes down Trump’s tariffs
Finance & Economy.detail: Despite the Supreme Court's ruling against President Trump's tariffs, Wall Street remained composed, with stocks experiencing a slight increase.

Technology.headline: Xbox chief Phil Spencer retiring after 38 years at Microsoft; Asha Sharma named new gaming CEO
Technology.detail: Phil Spencer, who reshaped Xbox through landmark acquisitions and a bet on cloud gaming, is stepping down after 38 years, and his successor, Asha Sharma, has roots in the Seattle startup community, with deep experience in consumer platforms.

Technology.headline: Microsoft Gaming Boss Resigns, Replacement Promises 'Return to Xbox'
Technology.detail: Asha Sharma, who replaces Phil Spencer, promised the 'return of Xbox,' though she didn't give a date for when any new physical hardware could be released.

Technology.headline: China defies global 'AI scare trade' as investors chase winners
Technology.detail: While U.S. markets are gripped by the "AI scare trade,” with investors selling software firms and wealth managers concerned that rapid advances in artificial intelligence will erode established business models, in China, the mood is far more upbeat as investors are chasing perceived winners.

Technology.headline: Bihar chasing future of technology UK AI minister
Technology.detail: UK Minister for AI and Online Safety Kanishka Narayan returned to Bihar on Saturday after more than two decades, exuding confidence that the State is “chasing the future of technology”.

Technology.headline: ASX 200 tech shares lead market sectors with a 7% bounce back
Technology.detail: ASX tech shares led the market last week with a 7% bounce back, which is a welcome bright spot for ASX 200 tech shares, which are in the midst of a prolonged rout. Investors are worried about high tech stock valuations, extraordinary AI capex, and whether AI could white-ant SaaS companies.

Science.headline: NASA's Artemis II mission to send humans around the moon delayed after last-minute rocket problem
Science.detail: NASA has delayed the March 6 launch of Artemis II after engineers found a helium flow problem during final checks; the mission aims to send four astronauts around the Moon for a 10-day journey but will not land on the Moon.

Science.headline: Study finds that women experience pain for longer
Science.detail: Research in *Science Immunology* shows women experience exacerbated chronic pain compared to men, potentially explained by biological differences in the immune system, which may lead to more equitable care for women as the science advances.

Science.headline: Scientists develop first-of-its-kind antibody to block Epstein Barr virus
Science.detail: Scientists have developed a novel antibody designed to block the Epstein-Barr virus.

Science.headline: Doctors Implant Dopamine-Producing Stem Cells in Parkinson's Patients
Science.detail: A clinical trial is underway to test whether engineered stem cells can restore dopamine production in the brains of people with Parkinson's disease, by implanting lab-grown cells directly into the brain.

Science.headline: Halting irreversible changes to Antarctica depends on choices made today
Science.detail: Choices made today are critical in halting irreversible changes to Antarctica.

Health.headline: WHO warns of collapse of Sudan's health system amid attacks on facilities
Health.detail: The World Health Organization (WHO) warned that Sudan's health system is on the brink of collapse due to ongoing attacks that continue to claim the lives of health workers and patients, with 37% of health facilities out of service. Health facilities have faced four attacks during February alone.

Health.headline: Single vaccine could protect against all coughs, colds and flus, researchers say
Health.detail: A single nasal spray vaccine could protect against all coughs, colds and flus, as well as bacterial lung infections, and may even ease allergies, say US researchers. The team at Stanford University have tested their 'universal vaccine' in animals and still need to do human clinical trials.

Health.headline: Patients exposed to superbugs by NHS safety breaches
Health.detail: Thousands of NHS patients were exposed to superbugs by doctors using unsafe operating gowns. A mass recall of surgical gowns and drapes is under way after it was found they had failed to meet safety standards, affecting some 150 NHS trusts.

Health.headline: A tampon could help improve early diagnosis of ovarian cancer
Health.detail: A specialist medical tampon could be used to help diagnose ovarian cancer earlier, researchers believe. If the cancer is caught in the early stages a woman has a 95 per cent chance of surviving the disease.

Health.headline: Social media can be addictive even for adults, but there are ways to cut back
Health.detail: It was found that social media can be addictive even for adults, but there are ways to cut back.

Sports.headline: Jacobs' Canada beat Britain to win Olympic men's curling gold
Sports.detail: Canada defeated Britain to win the gold medal in men's curling at the Winter Olympics. This victory adds to Canada's impressive record in Olympic curling.

Sports.headline: Manchester City close gap on Arsenal after O'Reilly sinks Newcastle in EPL
Sports.detail: Manchester City narrowed the gap on Arsenal in the English Premier League after Nico O'Reilly's goals secured a win against Newcastle. The victory moves Manchester City closer to the top of the league standings.

Sports.headline: Young short trackers taking valuable lessons from Olympic debut
Sports.detail: Young members of the Korean men's national short track speed skating team gained valuable experience at the Milan-Cortina Winter Games, with Rim Jong-un winning bronze in the 1,000 meters and silver in the 5,000m relay. Despite not fully meeting expectations, the young skaters appreciated the experience and camaraderie.

Sports.headline: Finland soothe sting of semi-final defeat with bronze medal
Sports.detail: Finland's men's Olympic ice hockey team recovered from a semi-final loss to beat Slovakia 6-1 and win the bronze medal. After a rocky start to the tournament, the team regrouped to secure the bronze.

Sports.headline: Pallekele weather update today, Sri Lanka vs England T20 World Cup 2026: Will rain affect ENG vs SL Super 8 match in Kandy?
Sports.detail: The weather forecast in Pallekele is being closely monitored to determine if rain will impact the T20 World Cup 2026 Super 8 match between Sri Lanka and England. The weather conditions could play a significant role in the outcome of the match.

Entertainment.headline: Willie Colón, best known for his Salsa tunes, passes away at 75
Entertainment.detail: Willie Colón, a musical legend and pioneer of Salsa music, has died at the age of 75. His family announced his passing, noting he died peacefully surrounded by loved ones.

Entertainment.headline: Eric Dane, 'Grey's Anatomy' star diagnosed with ALS, dies at 53
Entertainment.detail: Eric Dane, known for his role in 'Grey's Anatomy', passed away at 53 after battling amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS), a diagnosis he announced in April 2025. Celebrities and former co-stars have expressed their grief and pride in his 'heroic' battle against ALS.

Entertainment.headline: Nicole 'Snooki' Polizzi Reveals Cervical Cancer Diagnosis
Entertainment.detail: 'Jersey Shore' star Nicole "Snooki" Polizzi shared in a TikTok video that she has been diagnosed with stage 1 cervical cancer following a post-op appointment for a cone biopsy. She assured fans that the cancer was caught early.

Entertainment.headline: KH x RK Reunion: Kamal Haasan-Rajinikanth join hands for Nelson's film; shoot begins soon
Entertainment.detail: Kamal Haasan and Rajinikanth are reuniting for Nelson Dilipkumar's film, with shooting scheduled to commence shortly. This collaboration brings together two iconic figures of Indian cinema.

Entertainment.headline: Assi vs Do Deewane Seher Mein box office collection: Mrunal Thakur & Taapsee Pannu films run parallel, earns Rs…
Entertainment.detail: Mrunal Thakur and Siddhant Chaturvedi's 'Do Deewane Seher Mein' is competing with Taapsee Pannu's 'Assi' at the box office, with both films earning similar amounts. The films are running in parallel in terms of earnings.

Crime & Justice.headline: Gunmen on motorcycles kill at least 50 in northwest Nigeria: Report
Crime & Justice.detail: Gunmen on motorcycles killed at least 50 people in northwest Nigeria, according to reports. The report comes as police widen investigations into former prince, including questioning his close protection teams.

Crime & Justice.headline: Two killed, 3 critical after shooting at hockey rink in US's Rhode Island
Crime & Justice.detail: An attacker opened fire at an ice hockey rink in Rhode Island, killing two and leaving three in critical condition before dying from a self-inflicted gunshot wound.

Crime & Justice.headline: 3rd arrested in violent overnight home invasion; multiple illegal aliens accused of sexual assault, kidnapping
Crime & Justice.detail: Multiple illegal aliens are accused of sexual assault and kidnapping after a violent overnight home invasion where a third suspect has been arrested. ICE detainers were placed on two of the suspects.

Crime & Justice.headline: Elementary school forced into lockdown after stolen car pursuit in Mesa: police
Crime & Justice.detail: A 21-year-old suspect was arrested after allegedly stealing a car and fleeing from Mesa Police, before forcing an elementary school into lockdown.

Crime & Justice.headline: UK weighs removing ex-Prince Andrew from succession line amid Epstein probe
Crime & Justice.detail: The UK is considering removing ex-Prince Andrew from the line of succession amid the ongoing Epstein probe. This consideration arises as police broaden their investigations into the former prince, including questioning his close protection teams.

Education.headline: Union Minister visits schools and university in Pathein
Education.detail: Union Minister for Education Dr. Chaw Chaw Sein visited Pathein No.1 Basic Education High School, emphasizing high Grade-12 pass rates and secure administration of upcoming exams, while also highlighting curriculum updates for Grades 6 to 9.

Education.headline: Calls for urgent action on community preschool pay after Fair Work recommendation
Education.detail: The NSW Government is facing renewed pressure to increase funding for community preschools after the Fair Work Commission supported a union push to raise wages for early childhood teachers and educators, potentially worth up to $17,500 for some educators.

Education.headline: AI Boosts English Speaking Learning as Education Authority Upgrades Testing System to Enhance Practical Expression
Education.detail: The education authority in Taiwan has upgraded the English Self-Assessment System by integrating AI technology to enhance speaking tests, helping students improve their English communication skills, from elementary school through higher education. The system includes open-ended question types and real-time AI scoring to analyze pronunciation, fluency, and the relevance of responses.

Education.headline: School Assembly News Headlines Today (February 22): Top National, Business News, Sports News, Education News & World News with Weather Updates & Thought of the Day
Education.detail: The Sunday Guardian provides a news headlines about national, business, sports, education and world news, also including weather updates. Delhi is expected to have mostly clear weather with temperatures between 29°C and 30°C.

Education.headline: New Brunswick elementary school battles closure concerns ahead of potential budget cuts
Education.detail: An elementary school in New Brunswick is facing potential closure due to upcoming budget cuts. This is part of a broader trend of schools facing funding challenges and potential closures.

Lifestyle.headline: Pelicot's memoir launches in 22 languages, turning horror into hope for survivors
Lifestyle.detail: Gisele Pelicot's memoir about surviving sexual assault was released in 22 languages, offering hope and support to other survivors; her case also led to a new law in France defining rape and sexual assault as any non-consensual sexual act. In December 2024, Pelicot's ex-husband, Dominique Pelicot, and 50 other men were convicted of sexually assaulting her between 2011 and 2020 while she was under chemical submission.

Lifestyle.headline: The retirement no one warns you about is the one where you finally have time but no one has time for you
Lifestyle.detail: Retirement promises freedom, but many retirees are unprepared for the reality that their working friends and family become too busy to connect, leading to feelings of loneliness. Reimagining togetherness and finding value in small moments of connection can help transform this solitude into an opportunity for personal growth.

Lifestyle.headline: Nightly bathroom habit was missed sign of common men's cancer: 'I didn't know'
Lifestyle.detail: A dad ignored his frequent nightly bathroom trips until a routine PSA test led to a shocking prostate cancer diagnosis and life-saving treatment. The man's story highlights the importance of not ignoring health issues and getting regular checkups.

Lifestyle.headline: Brain training reduces dementia risk by 25% over 20 years, long-term study finds
Lifestyle.detail: A long-term study found that cognitive speed training shows lasting protection against Alzheimer's disease, reducing dementia risk by 25% over 20 years. The findings suggest that brain training can be an effective way to maintain cognitive health as people age.

Lifestyle.headline: Working in AI lifted their compensation; now they want prenups
Lifestyle.detail: As compensation increases due to working in AI, some are seeking prenuptial agreements. This reflects how changing economic landscapes influence personal and legal decisions.

Opinion/Editorial.headline: Trump raises new global tariff from 10% to 15%
Opinion/Editorial.detail: U.S. President Donald Trump announced he would raise the global tariff to 15%, increasing it from the 10% he initially declared after a setback from the Supreme Court. He stated this decision was effective immediately.

Opinion/Editorial.headline: Burdensome and outdated tax
Opinion/Editorial.detail: An editorial discusses the Philippine travel tax, which is being reviewed for potential abolishment. The travel tax was first imposed 70 years ago, in 1956, and legislative proposals to abolish the tax were met with public support.

Opinion/Editorial.headline: March to war?
Opinion/Editorial.detail: An editorial discusses the combustible atmosphere in the Gulf, with a massive American military build-up around Iran signaling potential conflict. The piece is part of the newspaper's opinion section.

Opinion/Editorial.headline: US' expanding aggression indicates PH, world are in danger
Opinion/Editorial.detail: The article asserts the US is showing cracks in its financial, technical, business and military spheres and is using a panicked, random approach to reassert control by coercion and invasion. It also mentions the Jeffrey Epstein scandal's impact on world elites allied with the West.

Opinion/Editorial.headline: Despite government blowing $100 billion, Americans reject mass transit
Opinion/Editorial.detail: An editorial discusses how Americans are rejecting mass transit despite the government spending over $100 billion on trolleys, streetcars, buses, and subways since 2020. It suggests that the government's scheme of election map gerrymandering is not working.

World.headline: Trump Raises Global Tariff To 15 Pct After US Supreme Court Ruling
World.detail: Following a Supreme Court ruling against his existing tariff measures, President Donald Trump announced he will raise the new global tariff to 15 percent. The tariffs will reportedly be imposed on Tuesday for at least 150 days.

World.headline: Pakistan carries out strikes in Afghanistan after spate of suicide attacks
World.detail: Pakistan conducted strikes in Afghanistan targeting militant hideouts along the Afghan border after a surge in deadly attacks. The action comes in response to recent suicide attacks within Pakistan.

World.headline: Australian warship transits Taiwan Strait, tracked by China's Navy
World.detail: An Australian warship transited the Taiwan Strait, and its movements were tracked by China's Navy. The transit occurred amid ongoing tensions in the region.

World.headline: Ukraine explosions kill policewoman, wound 15 in 'terror' attack
World.detail: Explosions in Ukraine resulted in the death of a policewoman and injuries to 15 others in what authorities are calling a 'terror' attack. The incident underscores the ongoing security challenges in the country.

World.headline: Myanmar National Airlines passenger aircraft damaged in drone attack
World.detail: A Myanmar National Airlines passenger aircraft sustained minor damage from a suicide drone attack at Myitkyina Airport in Kachin State. The incident occurred as the plane was preparing for departure.

Zimbabwe.headline: Zimbabwe Launches Tamper-Proof Platform To Smash Fake Qualification Scourge
Zimbabwe.detail: Zimbabwe has launched a tamper-proof platform to combat the issue of fake qualifications in the country, aiming to ensure the authenticity of academic credentials and enhance trust in the education system. The platform uses advanced technology to verify and secure qualifications, making it difficult to forge or alter them.

Zimbabwe.headline: Bulawayo Man, 21, Jailed 40 Years After Raping Granny, 81, And Falling Asleep In Her Bed
Zimbabwe.detail: A 21-year-old man from Bulawayo has been sentenced to 40 years in prison for raping an 81-year-old woman and then falling asleep in her bed. The incident has sparked outrage and highlights the severity of sexual assault cases in the region.

Zimbabwe.headline: Constitutional amendment makes diaspora vote possible — Ziyambi
Zimbabwe.detail: Zimbabweans living abroad will be able to vote in national elections once the recently gazetted Constitutional Amendment No. 3 Bill of 2026 is passed and attendant changes to the Electoral Act are made, according to Justice Minister Ziyambi Ziyambi. The proposed changes to Section 92 will result in a parliamentary process for electing the President.

Zimbabwe.headline: Shuntai Investments Targets 40 % Share of Zimbabwe's Cement Market by 2027
Zimbabwe.detail: Emerging cement producer Shuntai Investments has announced plans to capture up to 40% of Zimbabwe's cement market by 2027. The company's expansion signals growing confidence in the country's construction sector.

Zimbabwe.headline: Blessed Mhlanga: When speaking in Geneva becomes a crime in Harare
Zimbabwe.detail: For Zimbabwean citizen Blessed Mhlanga, speaking in Geneva is perceived as a crime in Harare, highlighting the tense political climate and scrutiny of state conduct. This suggests potential repercussions for individuals expressing dissenting opinions on international platforms.
